The most efficient way to draw boxes on the game client of Endless Online, which is written in C++, would be to use a graphics library like SDL or OpenGL.

Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do this using the SDL library:

1. Download and install the SDL library from https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php.
2. In your game project, include the SDL headers at the top of your source file:
```cpp
#include <SDL.h>
```

3. Then, initialize SDL in your main function:
```cpp
if (SDL_Init(SDL_INIT_VIDEO) < 0)
{
    printf("SDL could not initialize! SDL_Error: %s\n", SDL_GetError());
    return 1;
}
```

4. Create a window and a renderer for drawing:
```cpp
SDL_Window *sdlWindow = SDL_CreateWindow("Endless Online",
        SDL_WINDOWPOS_UNDEFINED, SDL_WINDOWPOS_UNDEFINED,
        800, 600, SDL_WINDOW_SHOWN);
if (!sdlWindow)
{
    printf("The window could not be created! SDL_Error: %s\n", SDL_GetError());
    return 1;
}

SDL_Renderer *sdlRenderer = SDL_CreateRenderer(sdlWindow, -1,
        SDL_RENDERER_ACCELERATED | SDL_RENDERER_PRESENTVSYNC);
if (!sdlRenderer)
{
    printf("The renderer could not be created! SDL_Error: %s\n", SDL_GetError());
    return 1;
}
```

5. Create a function that can draw a box for you:
```cpp
void draw_box(SDL_Renderer *renderer, int x, int y, int w, int h, SDL_Color color)
{
    SDL_Rect rect = { x, y, w, h };
    SDL_SetRenderDrawColor(renderer, color.r, color.g, color.b, color.a);
    SDL_RenderFillRect(renderer, &rect);
}
```

6. In your game loop, clear the screen, draw the box, and present the rendered content:
```cpp
SDL_Color boxColor = { 255, 0, 0, 255 }; // Red color
SDL_Event e;
bool running = true;
while (running)
{
    // Clear the screen
    SDL_SetRenderDrawColor(sdlRenderer, 0, 0, 0, 255);
    SDL_RenderClear(sdlRenderer);

    // Draw the box
    draw_box(sdlRenderer, 50, 50, 100, 100, boxColor);

    // Render to the screen
    SDL_RenderPresent(sdlRenderer);

    // Check for SDL events
    while (SDL_PollEvent(&e))
    {
        if (e.type == SDL_QUIT)
        {
            running = false;
        }
    }
}
```

7. Finally, clean up the SDL resources when the game is closed:
```cpp
SDL_DestroyRenderer(sdlRenderer);
SDL_DestroyWindow(sdlWindow);
SDL_Quit();
```

After following these steps, you should have an SDL window with a red box drawn in it. Adapt the code as needed for your specific project requirements.

