Optimizing Solidity with Yul involves using inline assembly inside your Solidity code to perform certain tasks more efficiently than possible with Solidity alone. This technique can minimize gas costs and improve the performance of your smart contracts.

To optimize your Solidity code with Yul, follow the steps below:

1. Identify areas of optimization: Analyze your Solidity code and look for sections that require gas optimization or compute-intensive tasks that lower-level code could perform more efficiently.

2. Use inline assembly: Introduce inline assembly blocks in your Solidity code where appropriate. Use the `assembly { ... }` construct to include Yul code. Here's an example of using inline assembly to add two numbers more efficiently:

